    {"repo": "sg-evals/chromium--2d05e315", "path": "third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/paint_controller.h", "symbol": "PaintController"}
  ],
  "text": "The Blink rendering pipeline from CSS style to paint involves these key files:\n\n1. **StyleResolver** (`third_party/blink/renderer/core/css/resolver/style_resolver.h` / `.cc`): The `StyleResolver` class resolves computed styles for DOM elements. It has a 1-1 relationship with `Document` and processes the document's collection of stylesheets (user, author, and UA styles) to produce final `ComputedStyle` objects for elements.\n\n2. **LayoutObject** (`third_party/blink/renderer/core/layout/layout_object.h`): The `LayoutObject` class is the base class for the layout tree. Every element that gets rendered has a corresponding `LayoutObject` (or subclass like `LayoutBlock`, `LayoutText`, etc.) that computes geometry/position based on the computed style.\n\n3. **PaintLayer** (`third_party/blink/renderer/core/paint/paint_layer.h`): The `PaintLayer` class (which extends `DisplayItemClient`) represents the painting layer abstraction. It is created for `LayoutBoxModelObject` elements that require a layer (e.g., positioned, transformed, or composited elements). It orchestrates painting of itself and its children.\n\n4. **DisplayItemList** (`third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/display_item_list.h`) and **PaintController** (`third_party/blink/renderer/platform/graphics/paint/paint_controller.h`): `DisplayItemList` is a container for `DisplayItem` objects that records paint operations. `PaintController` manages the painting process, caching display items and coordinating with `GraphicsContext` to produce the final paint artifact. At the Chromium compositor level, `cc/paint/display_item_list.h` defines the `DisplayItemList` used for rasterization."
}

